19/08/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Six illegal immigrants drowned when their boat sank off the Turkish coast near Izmir province on Friday (August 17th).
Rescue crews are searching for five others who are missing.
At least 45 passengers survived and are described as mostly Afghan nationals trying to reach Greece.
The captain of the vessel and its owner were arrested.
In other news, at least 16 people died and 14 were injured in a road accident early Saturday in southeast Turkey.
It happened in the province of Sanliurfa, when a lorry carrying farmers and their children hit another lorry.
Local laws ban lorries from transporting people.
(Reuters - 18/08/07;
AFP, AP, Sabah, Anadolu news agency, Dogan - 17/08/07)
